President Biden held a meeting with Republican Senators Capito, Barrasso, Blunt, Crapo, Toomey, and Wicker to discuss the need for investment in American infrastructure. These Senators are ranking members of various Senate committees related to the environment, energy, finance, banking, and transportation. The President emphasized his commitment to funding infrastructure to benefit the middle class and help the economy recover from the pandemic. He expressed his desire for real progress on a potential bipartisan deal by Memorial Day and stated that inaction was not acceptable. The President and the Senators agreed to stay in touch and continue discussions, with further communication at the staff level. This meeting followed a productive discussion with bipartisan congressional leaders on infrastructure.